      • write

        void write(byte[] data,
         int offset,
         int length)
           throws IOException
        Writes specified number of bytes to the output
        Parameters:
        data - the array to read bytes from
        offset - the offset in supplied array to start reading from
        length - the number of bytes to read (exactly)
        Throws:
        IOException - if I/O error occurred (for example - if number of actually written bytes is not equal to length)
